<snippet>
	<content><![CDATA[const indexOfAll = (arr, val) => {
  const indices = [];
  arr.forEach((el, i) => el === val && indices.push(i));
  return indices;
};]]></content>
	<description>Returns all indices of `val` in an array. If `val` never occurs, returns `[]`.  Use `Array.forEach()` to loop over elements and `Array.push()` to store indices for matching elements. Return the array of indices.</description>
